*Note: SNPS vcs & verdi license is required

//TB Directory
├── filelist_dv.f (DV filelist)
├── filelist_rtl.f (RTL filelist)
├── run.csh (run script)
├── seq
│   ├── FILES_test_seq.sv
│   ├── soc_base_vseq.sv
│   └── soc_seq_pkg.sv
├── SourceMe.csh (set env variables)
├── synopsys_sim.setup (set up different lib for RTL & DV)
├── tb
│   ├── tb_macro.sv (macros for testbench)
│   └── tb_top.sv (testbench top)
├── test
│   ├── soc_base_test.sv
│   └── soc_test_pkg.sv
└── vip (open source VIP)
    ├── ahb_vip
    ├── apb_vip
    ├── axi_vip
    ├── i2s_vip
    ├── i3c_vip
    ├── jtag_vip
    ├── spi_vip
    └── uart_vip

//How to run
1. run.csh -compile rtl +define+<user_option> (run 1 time whenever RTL change)
Example: 
run.csh -compile rtl +define+SYNTHESIS
2. run.csh -compile dv +define+<user_option> (run 1 time whenever DV change)
Example:
run.csh -compile dv +define+DMA_STUB
3. run.csh -test <user_seq_name> -run_dir <user_outfeed> -fsdb (waveform option) -seed (random seed option) +<user_runtime_option>
Example:
run.csh -test soc_base_vseq_c -run_dir outfeed_base_vseq -fsdb -seed 1234 +DMA_APB_VIP_ACTIVE
